[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the recruitment bot.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-trial IRB-approved-content corpus governance as architectural primitive.** Each trial has its own IRB-approved content corpus with its own version, its own approval date, its own language and reading-level variants, and its own validity window. The bot delivers from the corpus; the bot does not freestyle.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-trial pre-screen-instrument formalization with deterministic scoring.** Each trial has its own IRB-approved pre-screen instrument with explicit branching logic, criterion-by-criterion deterministic scoring, and per-question IRB-approved language.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Coercion, benefit-promise, and standard-of-care-disparagement detection.** The bot's output safety detects coercive language, benefit-promise language, and language that disparages non-trial care.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Coordinator-handoff infrastructure with per-trial routing.** Each trial has its own research-coordinator team, its own coordinator queue, and its own escalation pathway. Coordinator-side capacity is sized to the bot's expected output.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **CTMS integration with structured pre-screen output.** The pre-screen disposition emits a structured record into the institution's CTMS, populating the candidate's pre-screen worksheet so the coordinator does not re-collect.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Do-not-contact discipline with operational enforcement.** Candidates who decline are not re-contacted for the same trial unless the IRB-approved plan specifies otherwise.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Research-context PHI handling with separately-governed storage where required.** Storage is in separately-keyed, separately-access-controlled enclaves per institutional policy.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation discipline as architectural primitive.** Every assertion is grounded in a cited IRB-approved content item with version preserved.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Conservative-bias-default policy.** When the bot is uncertain, when the candidate's responses are ambiguous, the response defaults to "let me connect you with a research coordinator."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement rate, pre-screen-completion rate, pass-rate, handoff-completion rate, downstream-enrollment rate, and equity metrics vary by language, channel, reading level, demographic. Per-cohort dashboards reviewed by research-quality leadership, operations, IRB liaison, and patient-engagement teams.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When the IRB-approved-content store, the pre-screen-instrument store, the CTMS integration, the coordinator-handoff queue, or any escalation pathway is unreachable, the bot degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble right now; here's how to reach the research team directly," with direct routing to the research coordinator.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
